renting, the management of money, family support and local engagement. By revealing the ordinary and extraordinary practices involved in constructing and managing family and relationships in circumstances of low incomes, the book will appeal to a wide readership, including policy makers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCost and standard of livingzNorthern Ireland. 0aPoor familiesxFinance, PersonalzNorthern Ireland. 0aPoor familiesxGovernment policyzNorthern Ireland. 0aPoor familiesxSocial conditionsy21st centuryzNorthern Ireland. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh1 aKelly, Grace, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311119642840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447318859423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447318859/original  a978-3-11-119642-8  Bristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles